						               													<description>A word game that can be played alone or with friends.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players work together for a high score by forming tough words, but they cannot communicate during their turns. On each player's turn they will say a word outloud that includes at least 2 different letters that are currently shown on the board (and not covered).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Then they'll choose one of the letters in that word and place a penny on it, heads side up. If the word includes 3 different letters fromm the board, then the penny is placed tails side up.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game ends immediately when one letter remains or a player cannot say a word that uses two letters. The last word cannot include a red letter.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;SCORE: The blue outside spaces are worth one point and the purple inside spaces are worth two points. Any spaces with tails are worth one extra point.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
